	   <tr><td colspan=2>Butcherblock is a really good zone.&nbsp;&nbsp;Travel advice to get there:<br><br>If you're in FP, you are probably in West FP.  Make your way to East Freeport and go to the docks.  Wait for the boat, get on, and go to Butcherblock.  When you get into Butcherblock, leave the docks and follow the road until it forks then turn left.  You will zone into Greater Faydark.  You're gonna have to shout for a bind, probably around Kelethin, the wood elf city, but you might be able to get someone to bind you right at the BB zone.  Now go back into BB and back to the crossroads, this is where it gets tricky.  Diagrams help.<br><br>There WAS a diagram here, but the forum system didn't appreciate my mapmaking skills =P  Go to EQ Atlas for a good map, you will see what I am talking about.<br><br>You want to be at the skeleton tower.  The one that spawns closest to the crossroads will not be assisted, so you might as well try your luck on that one.  My friend had an equal level bard when I was 5 so it was very easy for me, but these skeletons will probably pose a challenge to you.  A good map of BB will show you how to get to the druid ring.  5 of these skeletons spawn there and do not aggro if one is attacked.  With my bard friend, I got from 5 to 8 in one day.  At the druid ring you might be able to find SoW and some buffs if you are having trouble staying alive.<br><br>Denevian Gerosilex<br>34th Mage<br>Cazic-Thule<br>&nbsp;<br>34th Mage of Cazic-Thule<br>Member of The Chosen Elite<br>25th Druid of The Nameless<br></td></tr>
