	   <tr><td colspan=2>It depends on your situation and your level.&nbsp;&nbsp;I used the the earth pet up until 29, and I have been using the fire pet very successfully since then.  The earth pet does have massive hp but he roots, and when something is rooted it turns around to beat the hell out of whatever just rooted it.  Earth pet also has pretty slow regen (or a LOT of HP) so expect to be waiting a while or using your mana for heals.  Fire pet has a damage shield that does its level +1 damage, EXTREMELY useful as the fire shield does not count against the damage total.  Apparently at 39 fire pets regen really fast too.<br><br>Denevian<br>33rd Mage<br>Cazic-Thule<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
