	   <tr><td colspan=2>I used a similar tactic when I was younger, except with the air pet. I found that the built in fire shield of the fire pet didn't work too well when the creatures were pouding on me. :)<br><br>The great thing about the air pet while soloing is that on more than one occasion, that stun DD it has gave me just enough time to get off a Gate or hit the zone when I was in terrible trouble.<br><br>I don't care much for the earth pet while soloing because a fleeing monster, when rooted, will start fighting back. With the other pets, the monster will flee and still take a beating without sharing it with the pet.<br><br>Also, after you hit 20, I found that keeping both pet healing spells memorized greatly increased my chances of survival. The recycle times on the healing spells are spaced just in time for one to "open" just after you cast the other. You can basically keep a constant stream of healing on your pet in cases where you need your pet to melee and you can't nuke. (like when you're hunting in fire-resistant zones)<br>&nbsp;<br>Neferti Firecaller, The Elven Nation, <a href="http://www.TheElvenNation.com" target=_new>http://www.TheElvenNation.com</a></td></tr>
